olive oil
2.5 cup water
2 packet jasmine rice
3 clove garlic
1 unit carrot
1 bag green beans
1 packet Asian Greens
1 packet sesame seeds
1 packet mayonnaise
4 tsp sesame oil
2 tsp rice wine vinegar
⅓ cup plain flour
2 tsp salt
2 unit eggs
2 packet panko breadcrumbs
2 packet Crispy Shallots
2 packet pork schnitzels
1 tbs soy sauce

Add the water to a medium saucepan and bring to the boil. Add the jasmine rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce the heat to low. Cook for 12 minutes, then remove the pan from the heat and keep covered until the rice is tender and all the water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.

TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

While the rice is cooking, finely chop the garlic (or use a garlic press). Thinly slice the carrot (unpeeled) into batons. Trim the green beans. Roughly chop the Asian greens. Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat. Add the sesame seeds and toast until browned, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a medium bowl. Add the mayonnaise, sesame oil and rice wine vinegar to the bowl with the toasted sesame seeds. Season to taste with salt and pepper and mix well to combine.

In a shallow bowl, combine the plain flour, the salt and a good pinch of pepper. In a second shallow bowl, whisk the eggs. In a third shallow bowl, place the panko breadcrumbs and crispy shallots. Separate the pork schnitzels. Dip each pork schnitzel first into the seasoned flour, followed by the egg and finally into the panko-shallot mixture. Set aside on a plate.

Return the frying pan to a medium-high heat with enough olive oil to coat the base of the pan. When the oil is hot, add 1/2 the crumbed pork and cook until golden and cooked through, 1-2 minutes each side. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towel and cover to keep warm. Repeat with the remaining crumbed pork.

TIP: Add extra oil between batches if needed.

Wipe out the pan and return to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Add the carrot, green beans and then a splash of water and cook, stirring, until tender, 4-5 minutes. Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Add the Asian greens and soy sauce and cook, stirring, until softened, 2 minutes.

Thickly slice the pork schnitzels. Divide the jasmine rice between bowls and top with the crumbed pork and soy veggies. Drizzle over the sesame dressing.